OL,5, Five top non-governmental organisations
OL,6, (NGOs) have suspended work in          
OL,7, Afghanistan after women were banned    
OL,8, from working for them by the Taliban.  
OL,10,FCare International, the Norwegian      
OL,11,FRefugee Council (NRC) and Save the     
OL,12,FChildren said they could not continue  
OL,13,Ftheir work "without our female staff". 
OL,15,FThe International Rescue Committee also
OL,16,Fsuspended services while Islamic Relief
OL,17,Fsaid it was stopping most of its work. 
OL,19,FAfghanistan's ruling Taliban have been 
OL,20,Fsteadily repressing women's rights.    
